Author: Gateway#3763
Content:
[telegram] <Regnar> Exchanges set their own confirmation numbers. If I run a hot wallet and you deposit to it, I can decide to credit you the funds when they're in the mempool or set an arbitrary number of confirmations. It's the wallet provider that decides that. If you do wallet to wallet, with wallets you actually own keys to, it would be nearly instant. Gotta get out of the mindset that a block confirmation time has anything to do with when you have access to it on an exchange... because it's outright incorrect (re @David: 1 minute = 1 confirmation

between 60 minutes (1 hour) = 2h06 waiting ...
